Police say they are still looking for other possible suspects who may have been involved in Monday&#8217;s violence. JOHANNESBURG - Three suspects arrested for looting shops belonging to foreign nationals in Atteridgeville in Tshwane have been denied bail. The three men were arrested on Monday. They appeared in the Atteridgeville Magistrates Court on Wednesday. Police say they are still looking for other possible suspects who may have been involved in Monday s violence. The police s Bonginkosi Msimango said: We appeal to community members who are aware of people involved in that looting inform the nearest police station. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)